      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAGNIFICENT STORM NZ (5) has been too good in his two starts since spell, last time overcoming a back row draw to beat arch rival Minstrel home by 4.6m in the Pinjarra Cup at this venue last time. That took his record here to four from five including a win in this race last year. Returns to the front line and is hard to go past. BETTER ECLIPSE (1) has ground to make up on Magnificent Storm through his midfield finish in the Pinjarra Cup but he was drawn on the back row there so is much better served by the inside barrier and had been racing consistently prior. STAR CASINO NZ (2) worked to the front from a very wide barrier to win in the city last time. Goes well here and can be prominent from the good draw. GOLDEN LODE NZ (3) resumes off consistent form including a fourth in the WA Cup and a very close second to BETTER ECLIPSE when last seen in December. Yet to miss a place when fresh and draws well.",
